The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Film for solidarity 

 Tendulkar, Aamir 

 Mumbai, July 17 (PTI): All major television networks will simultaneously air a short film featuring Prime Minister Manmohan Singh and leading sports and film stars tomorrow to express solidarity with those affected by the serial train blasts in Mumbai.

 Over 30 television channels will show the two-minute film, Voices of India, at 6 pm and 9 pm. 

 The film, which encapsulates thoughts expressed by Prime Minister Manmohan Singh after visiting the victims on Friday, also features cricketer Sachin Tendulkar and actors Aamir Khan, Shah Rukh Khan, Fardeen Khan, Anil Kapoor, Yash Chopra, Preity Zinta, Karan Johar and Nana Patekar. 

 The networks that will participate in the simulcast include Doordarshan, STAR TV, Zee, Sony Television, Times Network, ETV, MTV, TV 18, NDTV and Janmat.

 Designed as a campaign for India, it is a citizens response to the terrorist attack on Mumbai, and the coming together of the television networks to air the film is a first-time ever (event), said a release from Wizcraft, which has put together the project along with MP Murli Deora.




